<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,296,320]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
The only species of the unique subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Verhoeff, 1901" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1901" box="[795,1164,295,320]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Cerabrachyiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[795,984,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Cerabrachyiulus</emphasis>
Verhoeff, 
<number box="[1105,1164,295,319]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1901.0">1901</number>
</taxonomicName>
; the only known 
<taxonomicName class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from these islands. It is almost the most frequent species on Karpathos Island (
<bibRefCitation author="Strasser" box="[1131,1289,332,356]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Strasser, K. (1970) Uber griechische Diplopoden (Griechenland, Korfu, Kreta, Ost - Agais). Senckenbergiana biologica, 51 (3 / 4), 235 - 253." type="journal article" year="1970">
Strasser 
<number box="[1229,1289,332,356]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the database of Fauna Europea the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[565,753,368,392]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Cerabrachyiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[565,753,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Cerabrachyiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is elevated to genus level (
<bibRefCitation author="Enghoff" box="[1055,1313,367,391]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Enghoff, H., Kime, R. D. (2009) Fauna Europaea: Diplopoda. Fauna Europaea version 2.0, http: // www. faunaeur. org. (accessed 17 August 2011)" type="journal article" year="2009">
Enghoff &amp; Kime 
<number box="[1253,1313,367,391]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but at the same time it is shown as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[589,743,404,428]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[589,743,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Until a genus revision is completed we suggest the combination 
<taxonomicName box="[201,523,440,464]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mueggenburgi">
<emphasis box="[201,523,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaphyllum mueggenburgi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
